 found mostly in dogs but also in cats and captive bats. In addition, we report the first case of D. canis infestation in a domestic ferret (Mustela putorius). All these mammalian hosts are related to human activities, and D. canis evolution may be a consequence of this relationship. The monophyletic Demodex clade showing closely related dog and human Demodex sequences also supports this likely hypothesis.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Sastre, Natalia", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Francino, Olga", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Curti, Joseph N.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Armenta, Tiffany C.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Fraser, Devaughn L.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Kelly, Rochelle M.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Hunt, Erin", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Silbermayr, Katja", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Zewe, Christine", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "S\u00e1nchez, Armand", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Ferrer, Llu\u00eds", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Shao, Renfu", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Biodiversity", "Mammalia", "Chiroptera", "Chordata", "Animalia", "bats", "bat"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/4b4d0fa94d0288546bf2715b78c740b8", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/1529d25fe684c714daa60e602e81292fc05e7ff222a314abc81dd62bb1199638", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/5435545/items/T533ZDLF", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/5435545/items/T533ZDLF", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/3ec9e96b54426d699b946f53146bfef6!/b17256-19720", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://md5/330417efcaa2560c9b8ebcd6fae17ce0", "relation": "isPartOf", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "10.5281/zenodo.1410543", "relation": "isCompiledBy", "resource_type": "soft